  "transcript": {
    "title": "Perrin v. United States",
    "sections": [
      {
        "turns": [
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": -16570800,
                  "id": 2717,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2717",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/warren_e_burger",
              "name": "Warren E. Burger",
              "last_name": "Burger",
              "length_of_service": 6304,
              "thumbnail": {
                "mime": "image/png",
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/warren_e_burger/warren_e_burger.thumb.png",
                "id": 32773,
                "size": 52511
              },
              "ID": 15073,
              "identifier": "warren_e_burger"
            },
            "byte_start": 103424,
            "byte_stop": 348453,
            "stop": 61.253,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 57.941,
                "text": "The case is submitted, we'll hear arguments next in Perrin against the United States.",
                "byte_stop": 335287,
                "byte_start": 103424,
                "start": 0
              },
              {
                "stop": 61.253,
                "text": "Mr. Boudin, I think you may proceed whenever you're ready.",
                "byte_stop": 348453,
                "byte_start": 335287,
                "start": 57.941
              }
            ],
            "start": 0
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 348453,
            "byte_stop": 1888005,
            "stop": 446.142,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 67.869,
                "text": "Mr. Chief Justice and may it please the Court.",
                "byte_stop": 374993,
                "byte_start": 348453,
                "start": 61.253
              },
              {
                "stop": 108.605,
                "text": "The issue in this case, one of statutory construction with constitutional implications is whether Congress in using the term \"bribery\" in 18 U.S.C. 1952, the Travel Act, intended to refer to bribery of public officials as used in the common law or rather included the term \"commercial bribery\" and that which is involved solely in this case.",
                "byte_stop": 537893,
                "byte_start": 374993,
                "start": 67.869
              },
              {
                "stop": 143.665,
                "text": "The Travel Act, this Court will recall, insofar as relevant here makes it a crime, a felony punishable by $5000 or five years in prison, $10,000 to use interstate commerce including the mails for the purpose of facilitating an unlawful activity and one of the unlawful activities described here is bribery.",
                "byte_stop": 678118,
                "byte_start": 537893,
                "start": 108.605
              },
              {
                "stop": 185.233,
                "text": "The facts not between before this Court, due to the limited certiorari, it is sufficient for me to say that the petitioner is a private consulting geologist who was convicted after a jury trial charged with participating in the bribery of a private employee of a private concern and that there appear to be two telephone calls and one interstate shipment of non-incriminating data involved in this case.",
                "byte_stop": 844361,
                "byte_start": 678118,
                "start": 143.665
              },
              {
                "stop": 211.714,
                "text": "Now, in construing the statute and it's the most interesting problem of statutory construction, we have here, the problem is to determine what Congress and only Congress intended in the bribery act, not to determine what a state intended or as Nardello to which I will refer later, points out with a state label was.",
                "byte_stop": 950314,
                "byte_start": 844361,
                "start": 185.233
              },
              {
                "stop": 214.672,
                "text": "What did Congress intend?",
                "byte_stop": 962121,
                "byte_start": 950314,
                "start": 211.714
              },
              {
                "stop": 226.171,
                "text": "In considering the intent of Congress, we have the familiar but controlling and important canons of construction in a case of this kind.",
                "byte_stop": 1008201,
                "byte_start": 962121,
                "start": 214.672
              },
              {
                "stop": 270.743,
                "text": "The first, of course, is whether the term \"bribery\" has plain meaning and I must say that the Government's arguments in bribery is not to be considered as common law formulation but it would to be determined by the Oxford Dictionary or Webster's, does not seem persuasive particularly if one realizes that if one pertains to the legal dictionaries like Bouvier or Black, one finds that they use the term bribery including the most recent addition of Black in the technical common law sense.",
                "byte_stop": 1186461,
                "byte_start": 1008201,
                "start": 226.171
              },
              {
                "stop": 291.493,
                "text": "Just to take one example of Black, I'll just read the first few lines, \"The offering, giving, receiving or soliciting of anything of value to influence action as official or in discharge of legal or public duty.\"",
                "byte_stop": 1269426,
                "byte_start": 1186461,
                "start": 270.743
              },
              {
                "stop": 319.235,
                "text": "In contrasting these two definitions, one has to remember Mr. Justice Holmes' statement which I read recently in -- in Justice Frankfurter's Cardozo lectures 30 years ago that Congress is presumed to have intended to use familiar, legal expressions in their familiar legal sense.",
                "byte_stop": 1380394,
                "byte_start": 1269426,
                "start": 291.493
              },
              {
                "stop": 329.216,
                "text": "So, I would say that on balance, we'd probably come out better in our construction, but let us turn to the legislative history.",
                "byte_stop": 1420309,
                "byte_start": 1380394,
                "start": 319.235
              },
              {
                "stop": 340.357,
                "text": "As Mr. Justice Marshall pointed out in the Rewis case, it is a very meager or limited legislative history.",
                "byte_stop": 1464926,
                "byte_start": 1420309,
                "start": 329.216
              },
              {
                "stop": 358.411,
                "text": "The hearings clearly indicate as Nardello says and Rewis says that this was an attempt by Attorney General Kennedy to give a package of organized crime legislation to the Congress.",
                "byte_stop": 1537128,
                "byte_start": 1464926,
                "start": 340.357
              },
              {
                "stop": 396.736,
                "text": "And there are statements made particularly in the course of the testimony before the Committee by Attorney General Kennedy himself and in a supplementary letter to Congressman Sellar signed by Deputy Attorney General, now Mr. Justice White, indicating that this was an organized crime statute and that shakedowns were used by organized crime.",
                "byte_stop": 1690415,
                "byte_start": 1537128,
                "start": 358.411
              },
              {
                "stop": 419.056,
                "text": "The interesting thing is that there is no testimony in the record and no claim by Attorney General Kennedy or by his assistant Mr. Miller of the criminal division, that organized crime ever used commercial bribery.",
                "byte_stop": 1779649,
                "byte_start": 1690415,
                "start": 396.736
              },
              {
                "stop": 446.142,
                "text": "And what there is in this record are two or three very interesting statements which we have quoted in our brief of Attorney General Kennedy in which the subject of bribery, the only times when it is mentioned in the course of the Senate and House hearings is always with reference to the bribery of government officials.",
                "byte_stop": 1888005,
                "byte_start": 1779649,
                "start": 419.056
              }
            ],
            "start": 61.253
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": 63612000,
                  "id": 2787,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2787",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States"
                },
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": 528094800,
