            },
            "byte_start": 1888005,
            "byte_stop": 1892080,
            "stop": 447.157,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 447.157,
                "text": "Mr. Boudin.",
                "byte_stop": 1892080,
                "byte_start": 1888005,
                "start": 446.142
              }
            ],
            "start": 446.142
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 1892080,
            "byte_stop": 1894588,
            "stop": 447.766,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 447.766,
                "text": "Yes sir, Your Honor.",
                "byte_stop": 1894588,
                "byte_start": 1892080,
                "start": 447.157
              }
            ],
            "start": 447.157
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": 63612000,
                  "id": 2787,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2787",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States"
                },
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": 528094800,
                  "id": 2788,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2788",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                  "date_end": 1125723600,
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/william_h_rehnquist",
              "name": "William H. Rehnquist",
              "last_name": "Rehnquist",
              "length_of_service": 12293,
              "thumbnail": {
                "mime": "image/png",
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/william_h_rehnquist/william_h_rehnquist.thumb.png",
                "id": 32786,
                "size": 46923
              },
              "ID": 15141,
              "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
            },
            "byte_start": 1894588,
            "byte_stop": 1959372,
            "stop": 463.961,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 463.961,
                "text": "Do you -- do you feel that the old card decisions of this Court of Mr. Justice Story Hudson, Goodwin and so forth help or hinder you when they say there is no federal common law of crimes.",
                "byte_stop": 1959372,
                "byte_start": 1894588,
                "start": 447.766
              }
            ],
            "start": 447.766
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 1959372,
            "byte_stop": 2119868,
            "stop": 504.091,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 468.538,
                "text": "I don't think they have any help or hindrance.",
                "byte_stop": 1977657,
                "byte_start": 1959372,
                "start": 463.961
              },
              {
                "stop": 502.618,
                "text": "They are merely statements that we -- federal code doesn't include common law crimes but they are not a reason why Congress does not turn to the common law definition and while the courts don't look to a common law definitions to determine what Congress had in mind and I think actually, that was done to some extent in -- in the Dunn case but I will come to that, Your Honor.",
                "byte_stop": 2113912,
                "byte_start": 1977657,
                "start": 468.538
              },
              {
                "stop": 504.091,
                "text": "As I say – sorry.",
                "byte_stop": 2119868,
                "byte_start": 2113912,
                "start": 502.618
              }
            ],
            "start": 463.961
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": 188200800,
                  "id": 2704,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2704",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                  "date_end": 1277787600,
                  "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/john_paul_stevens",
              "name": "John Paul Stevens",
              "last_name": "Stevens",
              "length_of_service": 12611,
              "thumbnail": {
                "mime": "image/png",
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/john_paul_stevens/john_paul_stevens.thumb.png",
                "id": 32732,
                "size": 62101
              },
              "ID": 15060,
              "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
            },
            "byte_start": 2119868,
            "byte_stop": 2143274,
            "stop": 509.951,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 509.951,
                "text": "In the legislative history, is there any reference to labor racketeering and bribery of labor officials (Voice Overlap) --",
                "byte_stop": 2143274,
                "byte_start": 2119868,
                "start": 504.091
              }
            ],
            "start": 504.091
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 2143274,
            "byte_stop": 2437517,
            "stop": 583.514,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 537.493,
                "text": "Yes, that the Government's -- that the Government in its brief made reference to some problems of labor corruption but the Court will note, which I have regrettably not noted in my reply brief, that that referred to a different bill, a different bill dealing with immunity which was before the Congress and which referred to labor and the Taft-Hartley law.",
                "byte_stop": 2253406,
                "byte_start": 2143274,
                "start": 509.951
              },
              {
                "stop": 543.445,
                "text": "It never -- there was never any reference in discussing this bill to labor racketeering.",
                "byte_stop": 2277230,
                "byte_start": 2253406,
                "start": 537.493
              },
              {
                "stop": 548.083,
                "text": "I hope the Court will read that record to see that I am correct.",
                "byte_stop": 2295829,
                "byte_start": 2277230,
                "start": 543.445
              },
              {
                "stop": 562.579,
                "text": "Now, the Government says by referring to current books that labor unions are -- labor -- sorry, that organized crime now does use commercial bribery.",
                "byte_stop": 2353821,
                "byte_start": 2295829,
                "start": 548.083
              },
              {
                "stop": 583.514,
                "text": "But it's a little hard to take a book written in 1972 or 1973 and to draw the conclusion that this Congress in 1961 and these committees were considering a subject they discussed, namely the use of commercial bribery by organized crime.",
                "byte_stop": 2437517,
                "byte_start": 2353821,
                "start": 562.579
              }
            ],
            "start": 509.951
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": -16570800,
                  "id": 2717,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2717",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/warren_e_burger",
              "name": "Warren E. Burger",
              "last_name": "Burger",
              "length_of_service": 6304,
              "thumbnail": {
                "mime": "image/png",
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/warren_e_burger/warren_e_burger.thumb.png",
                "id": 32773,
                "size": 52511
              },
              "ID": 15073,
              "identifier": "warren_e_burger"
            },
            "byte_start": 2437517,
            "byte_stop": 2441070,
            "stop": 584.402,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 584.402,
                "text": "Well, Mr. Boudin (Voice Overlap) --",
                "byte_stop": 2441070,
                "byte_start": 2437517,
                "start": 583.514
              }
            ],
            "start": 583.514
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 2441070,
            "byte_stop": 2445145,
            "stop": 585.418,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 585.418,
                "text": "Yes, Your Honor.",
                "byte_stop": 2445145,
                "byte_start": 2441070,
                "start": 584.402
              }
            ],
            "start": 584.402
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": -16570800,
                  "id": 2717,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2717",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/warren_e_burger",
              "name": "Warren E. Burger",
              "last_name": "Burger",
              "length_of_service": 6304,
              "thumbnail": {
                "mime": "image/png",
                "href": "https://api.oyez.org/sites/default/files/images/people/warren_e_burger/warren_e_burger.thumb.png",
                "id": 32773,
                "size": 52511
              },
              "ID": 15073,
              "identifier": "warren_e_burger"
            },
            "byte_start": 2445145,
            "byte_stop": 2496554,
            "stop": 598.263,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 598.263,
                "text": "What is the occasion for -- for the courts to dwell deeply into the legislative history unless it's assumed that the word \"bribery\" is ambiguus?",
                "byte_stop": 2496554,
                "byte_start": 2445145,
                "start": 585.418
              }
            ],
            "start": 585.418
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": null,
              "view_count": 0,
              "href": "https://api.oyez.org/people/leonard_b_boudin",
              "name": "Leonard B. Boudin",
              "last_name": "Boudin",
              "length_of_service": 0,
              "thumbnail": null,
              "ID": 34199,
              "identifier": "leonard_b_boudin"
            },
            "byte_start": 2496554,
            "byte_stop": 2975744,
            "stop": 718.07,
            "text_blocks": [
              {
                "stop": 599.428,
                "text": "Oh, yes.",
                "byte_stop": 2501151,
                "byte_start": 2496554,
                "start": 598.263
              },
              {
                "stop": 611.851,
                "text": "Well, I think that I must say that the word \"bribery\" here -- I would prefer to say that the word \"bribery\" has an absolutely clear meaning and should be considered in its common law definition.",
                "byte_stop": 2550888,
                "byte_start": 2501151,
                "start": 599.428
              },
              {
                "stop": 634.88,
                "text": "But as I balance the dictionaries and as I realize the history of bribery for so many years and the use in -- in the penal codes and the use by draftsman to which I will refer in a few minutes, you see that bribery has a very special limited official connotation.",
                "byte_stop": 2643048,
                "byte_start": 2550888,
                "start": 611.851
              },
              {
                "stop": 650.85,
                "text": "One for example, were to look at the federal criminal code as it existed in 1961, one would see that Chapter 11 refers to bribery, graft and conflicts of interests.",
                "byte_stop": 2706892,
                "byte_start": 2643048,
                "start": 634.88
              },
              {
                "stop": 659.532,
                "text": "And the one section there entitled \"bribery\" deals with Section 201 with the bribery of government officials.",
                "byte_stop": 2741582,
                "byte_start": 2706892,
                "start": 650.85
              },
              {
                "stop": 664.165,
                "text": "I would like to be able to say that the situation is absolutely clear.",
                "byte_stop": 2760182,
                "byte_start": 2741582,
                "start": 659.532
              },
              {
                "stop": 683.924,
                "text": "There is no dispute to what the word \"bribery\" means, but candor requires that we assess the situation and say, \"Yes, this term as used in the statute as ambiguous and that's why we turn to the legislative history and to the other canons which I will refer.",
                "byte_stop": 2839176,
                "byte_start": 2760182,
                "start": 664.165
              },
              {
                "stop": 718.07,
                "text": "Now, just to continue for a moment if I may, Mr. Chief Justice, with respect to legislative history, as I said, I don't think that given that the -- that a book written currently or even a book written earlier which was not before the Committee and which it didn't consider is very persuasive evidence as to the meaning of the word \"bribery\" and I prefer, if I may say so, the words of Judge Gurfein who wrote the Brecht opinion on which we rely in the Second Circuit and is described --",
                "byte_stop": 2975744,
                "byte_start": 2839176,
                "start": 683.924
              }
            ],
            "start": 598.263
          },
          {
            "speaker": {
              "roles": [
                {
                  "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                  "date_start": -16570800,
                  "id": 2717,
                  "href": "https://api.oyez.org/preson_role/scotus_justice/2717",
                  "type": "scotus_justice",
                  "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                  "date_end": 528094800,
                  "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States"
                }
              ],
              "view_count": 0,
